26/* This is the default implementation of a barrier synchronization mechanism
27 for libgomp. This type is private to the library. Note that we rely on
28 being able to adjust the barrier count while threads are blocked, so the
29 POSIX pthread_barrier_t won't work. */
30
31#ifndef GOMP_BARRIER_H
32#define GOMP_BARRIER_H 1
33
34#include <pthread.h>
35
36typedef struct
37{
38 gomp_mutex_t mutex1;
39#ifndef HAVE_SYNC_BUILTINS
40 gomp_mutex_t mutex2;
41#endif
42 gomp_sem_t sem1;
43 gomp_sem_t sem2;
44 unsigned total;
45 unsigned arrived;
46 unsigned generation;
47 bool cancellable;
48} gomp_barrier_t;
49
50typedef unsigned int gomp_barrier_state_t;
51
52/* The generation field contains a counter in the high bits, with a few
53 low bits dedicated to flags. Note that TASK_PENDING and WAS_LAST can
54 share space because WAS_LAST is never stored back to generation. */
55#define BAR_TASK_PENDING 1
56#define BAR_WAS_LAST 1
57#define BAR_WAITING_FOR_TASK 2
58#define BAR_CANCELLED 4
59#define BAR_INCR 8
60
61extern void gomp_barrier_init (gomp_barrier_t *, unsigned);
62extern void gomp_barrier_reinit (gomp_barrier_t *, unsigned);
63extern void gomp_barrier_destroy (gomp_barrier_t *);
64
65extern void gomp_barrier_wait (gomp_barrier_t *);
66extern void gomp_barrier_wait_end (gomp_barrier_t *, gomp_barrier_state_t);
67extern void gomp_team_barrier_wait (gomp_barrier_t *);
68extern void gomp_team_barrier_wait_end (gomp_barrier_t *,
69 gomp_barrier_state_t);
70extern bool gomp_team_barrier_wait_cancel (gomp_barrier_t *);
71extern bool gomp_team_barrier_wait_cancel_end (gomp_barrier_t *,
72 gomp_barrier_state_t);
73extern void gomp_team_barrier_wake (gomp_barrier_t *, int);
74struct gomp_team;
75extern void gomp_team_barrier_cancel (struct gomp_team *);
76
77static inline gomp_barrier_state_t
78gomp_barrier_wait_start (gomp_barrier_t *bar)
79{
80 unsigned int ret;
81 gomp_mutex_lock (&bar->mutex1);
82 ret = bar->generation & (-BAR_INCR | BAR_CANCELLED);
83 if (++bar->arrived == bar->total)
84 ret |= BAR_WAS_LAST;
85 return ret;
86}
87
88static inline gomp_barrier_state_t
89gomp_barrier_wait_cancel_start (gomp_barrier_t *bar)
90{
91 unsigned int ret;
92 gomp_mutex_lock (&bar->mutex1);
93 ret = bar->generation & (-BAR_INCR | BAR_CANCELLED);
94 if (ret & BAR_CANCELLED)
95 return ret;
96 if (++bar->arrived == bar->total)
97 ret |= BAR_WAS_LAST;
98 return ret;
99}
100
101static inline void
102gomp_team_barrier_wait_final (gomp_barrier_t *bar)
103{
104 gomp_team_barrier_wait (bar);
105}
106
107static inline bool
108gomp_barrier_last_thread (gomp_barrier_state_t state)
109{
110 return state & BAR_WAS_LAST;
111}
112
113static inline void
114gomp_barrier_wait_last (gomp_barrier_t *bar)
115{
116 gomp_barrier_wait (bar);
117}
118
119/* All the inlines below must be called with team->task_lock
120 held. */
121
122static inline void
123gomp_team_barrier_set_task_pending (gomp_barrier_t *bar)
124{
125 bar->generation |= BAR_TASK_PENDING;
126}
127
128static inline void
129gomp_team_barrier_clear_task_pending (gomp_barrier_t *bar)
130{
131 bar->generation &= ~BAR_TASK_PENDING;
132}
133
134static inline void
135gomp_team_barrier_set_waiting_for_tasks (gomp_barrier_t *bar)
136{
137 bar->generation |= BAR_WAITING_FOR_TASK;
138}
139
140static inline bool
141gomp_team_barrier_waiting_for_tasks (gomp_barrier_t *bar)
142{
143 return (bar->generation & BAR_WAITING_FOR_TASK) != 0;
144}
145
146static inline bool
147gomp_team_barrier_cancelled (gomp_barrier_t *bar)
148{
149 return __builtin_expect ((bar->generation & BAR_CANCELLED) != 0, 0);
150}
151
152static inline void
153gomp_team_barrier_done (gomp_barrier_t *bar, gomp_barrier_state_t state)
154{
155 bar->generation = (state & -BAR_INCR) + BAR_INCR;
156}
157
158#endif /* GOMP_BARRIER_H */
